## Project
- **Name**: tomifoci
- **What it is**: A Hungarian-language World Cup 2026 football prediction game (tippjáték). Players predict match scores, join a "Wizard of ODDS" odds-based 1/X/2 league, compete in a Swiss-format "Párbaj" head-to-head tournament, pick a favourite team, and track standings/group tables/bracket. It is a full Next.js rewrite of a prior Convex-based app (`Vb_Tippjatek_2026`). UI is Hungarian throughout; English only on the landing page and login.
- **Stack**: Next.js 16, React 19, TypeScript 5, Tailwind CSS v4, Drizzle ORM, Neon serverless Postgres, Vitest, pnpm, deployed on Vercel
- **Repo / Production**: Vercel project `tomifoci.xyz` (ID `prj_puazmV7xpKmtZATcUj7XfzE9hLtJ`); Neon DB `blue-poetry-39540165`

## Key Paths
- `app/(player)/` — all player routes: meccsek, tabella, wizard, parbaj, profil, csoportok, brackets, szabalyok
- `app/api/state/` — single public-state endpoint; everything the UI reads flows through here
- `app/api/cron/poll/` — Vercel cron every 15 min; polls LiveScore API for odds + FT results
- `lib/db.ts` — `loadPublicStateFromNeon` — master DB read that feeds the state endpoint
- `lib/client-state.ts` — `buildPublicState` — runs all game engines on every read
- `lib/engine/` — pure engines: `swiss.ts`, `wizard.ts`, `scoring.ts`, `match-meta.ts`
- `lib/livescore.ts` — `runLiveScorePoll`; polls odds + FT history; does NOT poll live in-progress scores
- `db/schema.ts` — Drizzle schema; key tables: `predictions`, `results`, `settings`; key KV buckets: `apiCache`, `wizardPicks`, `swissPairings`, `pinHashes`, `pushSubscriptions`
- `components/game-provider.tsx` — client-side polling + state distribution
- `CLASSIC_PARITY_PLAYER.md` — living parity audit (Round 2, 2026-06-29); canonical list of gaps
- `DESIGN_SPEC.md` — frozen design tokens and layout rules (BROADCAST palette)

## Goals & Current Work
- Reach full feature parity with the classic app; keep the launched game stable.
- **Real open items (from 2026-06-30 code review), sequenced cleanup→bugfix:**
  - **Cleanup C1**: dead duplicate scoring engine — `lib/engine/scoring.ts` (`computeAllScores`/`computeRankings`/`calcPts`/`getActiveFav`) has zero callers; `lib/client-state.ts` reimplements all of it (second `calcPts` at ~:507). Two impls WILL drift. Pick one.
  - **Cleanup C2**: three definitions of match data — `lib/fixtures.ts` MATCHES, `lib/engine/match-meta.ts` MATCH_META+KICKOFFS, `public/classic/data.js` (parsed via `runInNewContext`). Lock/display/scoring can disagree. Make one source of truth.
  - **Cleanup C3**: push pipeline inert — `sendPush()` never called (decide: wire into cron poll, or mark parked).
  - **Cleanup C4–C6**: unused `lib/db.ts` exports (`getImportedRow`, `importedRowCount`); duplicate `clampOdds` (`engine/wizard.ts:15` vs `api/wizard/route.ts:28`).
  - ~~**Bug S1 (HIGH security)**~~ ✅ **FIXED 2026-06-30**: added `verifyPlayerPinThrottled()` in `lib/throttle.ts`; `favorites`/`predictions`/`wizard`/`guard` all route through it, sharing ONE per-account lockout key with login. Not-provisioned (no hash) is not counted. Tests: `test/throttle.test.ts` (4). Added `vitest.config.ts` (`@` alias for tests).
  - ~~**Bug S2 (MED security)**~~ ✅ **FIXED 2026-06-30**: removed IP from throttle key — `x-forwarded-for` is client-controlled so including it let an attacker bypass per-account lockout by rotating the header. Key is now strictly `community:player`. Updated `lib/throttle.ts`, `player-pin/route.ts`, `change-pin/route.ts`.
  - ~~**Bug S3 (MED security)**~~ ✅ **FIXED 2026-06-30**: admin-gated claim code. `POST /api/admin/claim-code { code }` gates all first-login claims; login page shows a "meghívó kód" step when server returns `claim-required`. When no code is set in DB, claims are open (backward compatible).
  - ~~**Correctness: kickoffOdds**~~ ✅ **FIXED 2026-06-30**: `runLiveScorePoll` now reads previous `odds` and `kickoffOdds` from apiCache before each poll. Matches that drop from the fixtures feed (= kicked off) get their last-seen odds frozen into a cumulative `kickoffOdds` row. `repairOdds()` tier 1 (snapshot) is now live.
- Wizard profile toggles (opt-in/mirror/leave) on Profile page — still a parity gap to verify.

